All policies should require an expiration date and metrics by which to evaluate its impact to determine whether said policy should be upheld or discontinued.

The same people enacting policy to supplement the ethical values lost due to the deterioration of community cohesion do nothing to ensure that their positions are not sought by those running for all the wrong reasons (fame, fortune, and power).

Politicians should make no more than what they were making prior to holding office. Running for office should not be a lottery ticket to a higher lifestyle. Too many run for the prize money knowing they can hide behind the work of the other hundreds of representatives.
